abstract: >-
  agentdx is a framework-agnostic diagnostic SDK for detecting
  failure pathologies in AI agent systems. It provides a three-tier
  detection architecture (rule-based, ML classifier, LLM-as-judge)
  for identifying seven operational failure modes including context
  erosion, tool thrashing, instruction drift, recovery blindness,
  hallucinated tool success, goal hijacking, and silent degradation.
  The taxonomy aligns with the OWASP Top 10 for Agentic Applications
  and UC Berkeley's MAST framework.
